OL,6,FThis meant putting certain rules in
OL,7,Fplace that made life difficult for
OL,8,Fpeople who couldn't prove their right
OL,9,Fto live in the UK, like making
OL,10,Femployers, landlords, NHS staff and
OL,11,Fother public servants check people's
OL,12,Fimmigration status.
OL,14,FThe Equality and Human Rights
OL,15,FCommission said the measures broke
OL,16,Fequalities law, and negative
OL,17,Fconsequences of the policy were
OL,18,F"repeatedly ignored, dismissed, or
OL,19,Ftheir severity disregarded".
OL,1,Wz5~k4~k7}hw1 ~k4~sj5j5~s1 G     G7/17
